## Endpoint policies

An endpoint policy is a set of IAM-based permissions attached to a VPC endpoint that controls which AWS resources and actions can be accessed through the endpoint. It acts as an additional layer of security by allowing or denying specific requests, such as access to particular S3 buckets, even when network connectivity is already established.


I updated my endpoint's policy by changing the effect from Allow to Deny. I could see the effect of this right away, because when i ran the command to list my buckets in s3 it failed.

